00:11:02.790 --> 00:11:03.830
and behavior change,

00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:06.570
and that the two coincide.

00:11:06.570 --> 00:11:08.980
And just to end this
little tiny portion of it,

00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:11.320
so blindness is not an absence of light.

00:11:11.320 --> 00:11:13.840
Because this animal has a
functional respecification,

00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:16.917
changes in cortical and
subcortical connections,

00:11:16.917 --> 00:11:19.560
a really big magnification
of its verbrice,

00:11:19.560 --> 00:11:23.450
so its entire nervous system has been

00:11:23.450 --> 00:11:25.070
kind of rewired and reorganized

00:11:25.070 --> 00:11:26.930
based on this lack of sensory input.

00:11:26.930 --> 00:11:27.763
But that's pretty,

00:11:27.763 --> 00:11:29.630
that's sort of like taking a
sledgehammer to the system.

00:11:29.630 --> 00:11:31.240
Let me show you something
a little more subtle.

00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:33.460
This is natural differences
in rearing conditions,

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:35.690
cultural transmission of rearing style.

00:11:35.690 --> 00:11:36.630
And these are voles.

00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:38.090
Voles are biparental.

00:11:38.090 --> 00:11:39.790
They both, both parents rear their young.

00:11:39.790 --> 00:11:41.120
And we can measure differences

00:11:41.120 --> 00:11:43.540
in total tactile contact of the young.

00:11:43.540 --> 00:11:45.980
We look at high contact parents,
and low contact parents.

00:11:45.980 --> 00:11:47.370
And important to remember,

00:11:47.370 --> 00:11:50.320
is that high contact offspring
show differences in behavior,

00:11:50.320 --> 00:11:52.970
high contact offspring
become high contact parents,

00:11:52.970 --> 00:11:54.930
and if you cross foster
them on the day of birth,

00:11:54.930 --> 00:11:56.400
you take low contact parents

00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:57.880
and put them with high contact parents,

00:11:57.880 --> 00:11:59.240
they become high contact parents.

00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:02.350
So this is a social
transmission of a rearing style.

00:12:02.350 --> 00:12:03.650
And if we look at the connections

00:12:03.650 --> 00:12:04.820
of their somatosensory cortex,

00:12:04.820 --> 00:12:05.780
particularly in the regions

00:12:05.780 --> 00:12:07.600
of the body that are being touched,

00:12:07.600 --> 00:12:09.470
we see that connections
are mostly the same.

00:12:09.470 --> 00:12:12.500
This is an injection site, and
these are connections to it.

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:14.460
But we also see
differences in connections.

00:12:14.460 --> 00:12:15.800
And remember, this is pretty subtle.

00:12:15.800 --> 00:12:18.870
And differences in connections
of frontal cortex as well.

00:12:18.870 --> 00:12:20.760
So what factors contributed
to the phenotypes?

00:12:20.760 --> 00:12:23.760
So I'm just showing you a
much more subtle example

00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.050
of the role of sensory input

00:12:26.050 --> 00:12:28.430
in shaping the brain and
shaping connectivity.

00:12:28.430 --> 00:12:31.950
Well, genes definitely contribute
to cortical sheet size,

00:12:31.950 --> 00:12:33.910
cortical field size, cortical connections,

00:12:33.910 --> 00:12:35.220
peripheral morphology.

00:12:35.220 --> 00:12:37.810
And cellular mechanisms
involved in plasticity

00:12:37.810 --> 00:12:39.550
may be genetically specified,

00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:41.490
which allows the environment to impact

00:12:41.490 --> 00:12:42.750
some of these same things.

00:12:42.750 --> 00:12:44.980
I can change cortical field
size, cortical connectivity,

00:12:44.980 --> 00:12:47.690
peripheral morphology, which
I showed in these experiments.

00:12:47.690 --> 00:12:50.030
And I've given you examples
from the bill of the platypus,

00:12:50.030 --> 00:12:53.500
and I suggest that the same
thing is occurring in humans.

00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:54.333
But what about things

00:12:54.333 --> 00:12:56.840
like social learning,
language, and culture?

00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:59.810
I would suggest that the
best way to think about these

00:12:59.810 --> 00:13:03.290
as these are simply complex
patterns of physical stimuli

00:13:03.290 --> 00:13:05.170
that are impinging on the
developing nervous system.

00:13:05.170 --> 00:13:10.040
So mother's love is temperature,
touch, cadence of a voice,

00:13:10.040 --> 00:13:10.873
nothing more.

00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:14.920
And this can impact how
the brain wires itself.

00:13:14.920 --> 00:13:16.610
It can impact size of cortical fields,

00:13:16.610 --> 00:13:18.240
and connections of cortical fields.

00:13:18.240 --> 00:13:20.110
So I'm gonna end a little bit with this.

00:13:20.110 --> 00:13:22.840
This is a sort of a human evolution,

00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:23.850
not quite a cladogram.

00:13:23.850 --> 00:13:26.000
And on the bottom is
environment and social context,

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:29.530
and on the top, it's
sort of truncated here,

00:13:29.530 --> 00:13:32.980
is meant to be sort of
morphology or genes.

00:13:32.980 --> 00:13:35.570
And modern hand is proposed
to have been around this

00:13:35.570 --> 00:13:37.380
for about 700,000 years.

00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:39.120
But what's really pretty fascinating

00:13:39.120 --> 00:13:42.160
is that until recently,
we were using stone tools.

00:13:42.160 --> 00:13:46.010
So we had, and big brains
happened way back here, right?

00:13:46.010 --> 00:13:48.070
So we had the big brain,
we had the modern hand,

00:13:48.070 --> 00:13:50.550
but we were not doing what we're
doing with the modern hand.

00:13:50.550 --> 00:13:52.330
And if you believe that all behaviors

00:13:52.330 --> 00:13:53.330
is generated by the brain,

00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:55.490
and I believe that all behavior's
generated by the brain,

00:13:55.490 --> 00:13:57.000
then the brain must have changed.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:59.570
And if the brain didn't change
by changes in DNA sequence,

00:13:59.570 --> 00:14:02.200
it must have changes by
activity dependent mechanisms,

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:03.233
and/or culture.

00:14:05.630 --> 00:14:07.560
It's hard to believe that
the Industrial Revolution

00:14:07.560 --> 00:14:09.320
was less than 300 years ago.

00:14:09.320 --> 00:14:10.153
And if you look,

00:14:10.153 --> 00:14:11.970
we actually changed the
scape of this planet.

00:14:11.970 --> 00:14:14.360
And now we have daily and
prolonged interactions

00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:16.560
with computers, and machines, and tools,

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:17.940
really sophisticated tools.

00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:19.540
And I'll end by saying

00:14:19.540 --> 00:14:21.710
we are combinatorial creatures
constructed by genes,

00:14:21.710 --> 00:14:23.840
bodies, behaviors, and
environmental context.

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:26.270
And I think, you can look for the genes

00:14:26.270 --> 00:14:27.760
that are distinguishing humans,

00:14:27.760 --> 00:14:29.370
I think you're gonna find only a few,

00:14:29.370 --> 00:14:32.040
maybe some involved in
expansion of the neocortex.

00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:34.490
But humans have evolved
an extraordinary capacity

00:14:34.490 --> 00:14:35.790
to construct our neocortex

00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:38.890
over the course of a prolonged
infancy and childhood,

00:14:38.890 --> 00:14:41.000
allowing for rapid phenotypic change

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:42.380
even within a single generation.

00:14:42.380 --> 00:14:45.800
I would say that if Leah
Krubitzer born 30 years ago,

00:14:45.800 --> 00:14:49.240
or hundred years ago,
or 300,000 years ago,

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:50.900
I wouldn't be Leah Krubitzer,

00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:53.410
have kidney rock, or using a spear.

00:14:53.410 --> 00:14:55.130
I would be a different brain.

00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:57.170
We have a remarkable
fluid brain/body interface

00:14:57.170 --> 00:14:58.003
with the environment,

00:14:58.003 --> 00:14:58.890
such that tools and machines

00:14:58.890 --> 00:15:02.490
can extend our embodiment
and our peripersonal space

00:15:02.490 --> 00:15:04.390
and expand the loop between
our brains, our bodies,

00:15:04.390 --> 00:15:05.223
and the world.

00:15:05.223 --> 00:15:08.490
And I think this has made us
unique biohybrid creatures

00:15:08.490 --> 00:15:10.720
whose brains adapt and
bootstrap themselves

00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:12.880
with the technologies
that we give rise to,

00:15:12.880 --> 00:15:14.300
and for better or worse,

00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:16.830
with whom our futures are
increasingly entwined.

00:15:16.830 --> 00:15:18.029
Okay, thank you.

00:15:18.029 --> 00:15:21.029
(audience applauds)

00:15:22.895 --> 00:15:25.478
